<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-12-03T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-12-03T16:00:00-05:00" n="563" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d563">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">711.42157Sa29/643: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Canada</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Phillips</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Ottawa</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-12-03T16:00:00-05:00">December 3, 1929—4
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 8 p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>233. Legation’s 230, November 25, 8 p.m. Prime Minister informs me today
                            that neither Minister of Justice nor Doctor Skelton will return to
                            Ottawa in time to hold conference of Premiers before Christmas and that
                            accordingly the conference in question will not take place before
                            January.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
